Azure Container Instances (ACI)

1. ACI kya hai?

- Azure ka simplest container hosting service
- VMs manage karne ki zarurat nahi — sirf container image do, Azure chala dega
- Serverless — pay per second, jab container chal raha hai tabhi paise
- Best for: Simple apps, batch jobs, dev/test environments
- ACI vs AKS (Azure Kubernetes Service):


| ACI                           | AKS                                 |
| ----------------------------- | ----------------------------------- |
| Single container / small apps | Multiple containers / microservices |
| No orchestration              | Kubernetes orchestration            |
| Cheapest for simple use       | Costly but powerful                 |
| No auto-scaling built-in      | Auto-scaling, self-healing          |
| Fastest to deploy             | Complex setup                       |



Day 10 mein ACI use karenge (simple), Day 11 mein AKS (advanced/Kubernetes).

ACI create karna (Azure CLI):

az container create \
  --resource-group myRG \
  --name mytodoapp \
  --image myacr.azurecr.io/todoapp:latest \
  --cpu 1 \
  --memory 1 \
  --ports 80 \
  --ip-address Public


  